<br>
Second. Recently it has goten a bit better, but for awhile, reading the Battlefield was like reading a frigging bus schedule. We have 4 different groups who want to go do this mob, and three for that one, two over here, four back on this guy, and then 7 single targets, all in the same week. Someone once suggested a calender be made, but nobody ever got around to it. Personally I don't have time to try and remember what days which people want to hit certain mobs. Several times my guild (bunch of big time bad ass raiders that we are) refrained from hitting a certain target because one of us remembered such and such guild wanting to hit it. And then we waited...and waited...and waited...all the time doing a different target. Sometimes people post times they are going to go after a mob, but often it's just &quot;Chardok Royals, Aug 32nd&quot; Yeah great. When on the 32nd? If you say noon pacific, and at 12:15 I check and see 5 of your guiildies on, none in Chardock, what then?<br>
<br>
Then you get the guild who posts 6 things over the course of the next month. Taldaydar and I and someone from Reso already posted about the joke that this is. Why not just go in and post &quot;Chardock Royals, Everyday in September&quot;? (And I'm picking the Royals cause it seems to be a consistantly popular one..no other reason) Yes all examples can be taken to the extreme, but everybody has their own definition of extreme. <br>
<br>
Also, anybody who tells you that they can't switch targets in 15 minutes is either 1-lame 2-runs with lame people 3-has no clue what they are talking about. I will go back to my guild again. At the height of it's powers we had three porters. We never actually had all three on at once I don't ever think, so we ran everywhere and PoK'd it. Once we had our team together I could herd them to any place we wanted to hunt in 15 minutes, tops. Once we were together we could hit multiple targets no problem. If you can't switch targets, then it's because of apathy or inertia. Yes I understand you wanted the chanter epic piece from Fear. It is unlikely that there is not one more piece of gear that someone in your raid can't use from some other place. We went to Kael, it was busy, we opted out to Chardok, it was fine. We went to Chardok a different time, and they were having a convention, so we went to PoS. We went to kill Doomshade, but he was having dinner with Fennin Ro or something, so off to Ssra for some Rhag hunting. If you get locked in all that you get is frustrated and cranky. <br>
<br>
Jhary<br>
